The paper deals with the problem of characterizing the image size of a source, which is a topic related to information theory and signal processing. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the impact of the results on source networks and network problems, which suggests that it may be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper's focus on achieving optimal coding suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.SI (Systems and Control).
